1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,880
 Hello, I'm Justine. Today I'm going to tell you about a very bad weekend that I had this summer.

2
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:20,680
 But first I need to tell you four things to help give you some context

3
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:25,960
 to understand why the weekend was so bad.

4
00:00:26,840 --> 00:00:31,320
 The first thing is that I do not like driving.

5
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:38,360
 For many years I lived about half an hour away from the closest town.

6
00:00:38,760 --> 00:00:44,000
 Half an hour by car away from the closest grocery store,

7
00:00:44,680 --> 00:00:51,240
 the bank, you know, all the things you need to do to exist in our life.

8
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:56,440
 We lived half an hour away. So I had to drive all of the time.

9
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:02,000
 And once my kids got older, there was also activities to bring them to.

10
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:07,440
 And so driving for me has been an annoying chore,

11
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:14,280
 an annoying job that I've had to do for decades.

12
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:20,520
 I'm 37 years old. I have been driving since before I was allowed to have my driver's license.

13
00:01:21,880 --> 00:01:28,440
 Where I lived in Saskatchewan, we were allowed to get our driver's license at 16 years old.

14
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:34,399
 But I grew up on the farm. So I've been driving before I was even allowed to.

15
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:40,800
 So for many years, driving has felt really, really annoying to me.

16
00:01:41,960 --> 00:01:49,199
 The second thing you need to know is that my kids are now in a competitive swim club.

17
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:58,160
 So the sport that they're in is swimming and they practice and are pool in our town

18
00:01:58,680 --> 00:02:06,000
 with the rest of their team all summer, but they also have swim meets or swim competitions.

19
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:16,800
 So every weekend I drive to a different city around our town to bring my kids to their swim competitions.

20
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,480
 So there's more driving.

21
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:26,680
 The third thing is that my husband and I own a porta potty rental business.

22
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:28,160
 This is a porta potty.

23
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:40,560
 A porta potty is a plastic little building that you go to the bathroom in when there's no regular bathroom facilities available.

24
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:47,280
 So we have about a hundred of these porta potty or portable toilets.

25
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:53,200
 And we rent them out to all different types of businesses.

26
00:02:53,760 --> 00:03:01,920
 And this past summer, we had all of our porta potty rented out and then there was a forest fire.

27
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:15,519
 There was a forest fire close to our town and there was hundreds of firefighters that came from all over the country and even all over the world.

28
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:21,760
 There was some firefighters that came from Australia and some from the United States.

29
00:03:22,399 --> 00:03:28,560
 And so there was hundreds of firefighters that came to help put out the forest fire.

30
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:32,240
 And they needed porta potties.

31
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:35,600
 But it was the weekend.

32
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:44,400
 And the place where we buy the porta potties from is nine and a half hours of driving away.

33
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:50,400
 So the place to buy porta potties was not open and it was the weekend.

34
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:58,320
 So we stole a bunch of our porta potties back from all the different businesses that were renting them.

35
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:03,280
 So we needed about 15 porta potties for the forest fire.

36
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:08,560
 And so we took a bunch of porta potties away from the other businesses.

37
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:12,880
 For example, there was a construction crew that had four porta potties.

38
00:04:12,880 --> 00:04:15,600
 So we took two of their porta potties away.

39
00:04:16,079 --> 00:04:20,800
 We left them with two porta potties and then we took two back.

40
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:24,800
 And we took one from here and three from there and one from over there.

41
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:29,200
 And then we had enough porta potties to bring to the firefighters.

42
00:04:29,760 --> 00:04:35,200
 And we told all of these businesses, hey, sorry, we got an emergency.

43
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:42,640
 Everybody understands we need to keep these firefighters happy with their portable bathrooms.

44
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:47,760
 And we'll give you back your porta potties within a week.

45
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:51,440
 We will make it we will make it right as soon as we can.

46
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:53,840
 We're just in a big crunch.

47
00:04:53,840 --> 00:04:56,240
 We are having a big crunch time.

48
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,680
 It's a big problem right now.

49
00:04:58,320 --> 00:04:59,840
 And we'll get it sorted out.

50
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:01,040
 We just need these.

51
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:03,760
 We need to take them back from you just for a few days.

52
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:08,800
 So that's information number three.

53
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:13,600
 And information number four is that it was actually a long weekend.

54
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:19,200
 So in Canada at the end of July and the beginning of August,

55
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:21,440
 we have a long weekend.

56
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:25,760
 That means that there's an extra day on the end of the weekend.

57
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:28,640
 So Monday was a day off.

58
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:33,840
 So we could not buy porta potties until Tuesday.

59
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:42,560
 Another thing is that my kids had a really important swim competition that weekend.

60
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:47,840
 It was the last swim competition of the year before provincials.

61
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:52,640
 Provincials is when the best athletes from the province,

62
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:59,200
 the whole province all come together and compete at the last competition of the year.

63
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:04,159
 So this competition was the second last competition.

64
00:06:04,159 --> 00:06:10,239
 And it was the competition where everybody tries to swim as fast as they can

65
00:06:10,239 --> 00:06:12,400
 and make it to provincials.

66
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:15,679
 They want to make it into the top three swimmers

67
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:18,080
 so that they can get to provincials.

68
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:21,600
 So my kids really needed to go to this swim competition.

69
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:23,120
 So that's okay.

70
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:28,240
 We drove to the swim competition on Friday.

71
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:36,000
 And then I drove from the swim competition to the other city on Sunday and Monday.

72
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,000
 And then I bought the potties on Tuesday.

73
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,280
 And then I drove home.

74
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:42,160
 But this is how it all happened.

75
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:51,520
 So on Friday I drove two hours, two hours to the city where the swim competition was being held.

76
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:55,360
 And then my kids swim on Saturday and Sunday.

77
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:59,600
 And during the swim competitions I'm a volunteer.

78
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:03,600
 So all day long I'm helping run the swim meet.

79
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:07,440
 There's many, many parents that help to run the swim meet.

80
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:09,040
 And it's a lot of fun.

81
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:13,600
 We really enjoy working together and making the swim meet happen.

82
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:18,160
 And watching our kids do really well with their swimming.

83
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:23,120
 But it was 37 or 38 degrees Celsius.

84
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,480
 It was so hot.

85
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:25,600
 It was so sunny.

86
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,040
 And we were camping.

87
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:28,640
 We had a tent.

88
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:30,320
 And it was really hot.

89
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:35,760
 We ended up being able to sleep in a camper with our friends.

90
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:38,080
 And they had air conditioning.

91
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:41,840
 So that helped it not be quite so difficult.

92
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:44,640
 So we shared a camper with our friends.

93
00:07:45,280 --> 00:07:49,599
 And we slept in this other city on Friday night and Saturday night.

94
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:53,680
 Then my kids made it to provincials.

95
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:58,159
 My kids swam so well that they made it to the provincial competition.

96
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:04,159
 And that meant that on Monday they had an extra practice.

97
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:11,520
 All of the swimmers who made it to provincials stayed at the pool to have an extra practice

98
00:08:11,520 --> 00:08:12,480
 altogether.

99
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:14,960
 But I needed to go to Calgary.

100
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:18,560
 I needed to go to this other city to buy the porta-potties.

101
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:24,560
 So luckily my friends let my kids stay with them on Sunday night.

102
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:30,160
 And then my kids got a ride back to our house with these other friends.

103
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:34,240
 But on Sunday night I had to start my drive to Calgary.

104
00:08:35,040 --> 00:08:38,240
 So I was in a city called Camloops.

105
00:08:39,280 --> 00:08:43,760
 And Camloops is about seven hours away from Calgary.

106
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:46,480
 Or seven and a half hours away from Calgary.

107
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:56,240
 So my plan was to drive three or four hours and stay at a city called Revelstock overnight.

108
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:58,480
 And then continue my drive on Monday.

109
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:01,440
 Sleep in Calgary on Monday.

110
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:04,160
 Pick up the potties on Tuesday and then drive home.

111
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,800
 But that's not what happened.

112
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:15,280
 On Sunday night I started my drive and I got to Revelstock around 10 pm or 11 maybe.

113
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:19,760
 And I could not find a hotel room.

114
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:25,600
 It was Sunday night on a long weekend and I did not call a head.

115
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:32,320
 There was no, there's not enough time for me to plan ahead my hotel room.

116
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:38,560
 And so most of the hotel rooms in Revelstock had probably been booked four or five months ago.

117
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:43,200
 So Revelstock is a very busy tourist town.

118
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:46,240
 Everybody's enjoying beautiful British Columbia.

119
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:48,160
 Except for me.

120
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:49,840
 I could not find a hotel room.

121
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:53,040
 I went to every hotel I could find.

122
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,520
 And I called a bunch more hotels.

123
00:09:56,079 --> 00:09:58,400
 Some of them even laughed at me.

124
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:03,599
 When I called to ask if there was a room available for the night, they said,

125
00:10:04,719 --> 00:10:08,000
 no, it is Revelstock on a long weekend.

126
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,240
 There is no hotel rooms available.

127
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:10,959
 Are you kidding?

128
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,760
 No, I'm not kidding actually.

129
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:15,439
 I'm quite desperate.

130
00:10:15,439 --> 00:10:16,959
 But thanks anyway.

131
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:21,040
 So there was no place for me to sleep in Revelstock.

132
00:10:21,599 --> 00:10:27,040
 I was so tired after helping at the swim meet all weekend and having a long drive

133
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:29,439
 from Cameloups to Revelstock.

134
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,079
 I was really desperate.

135
00:10:32,079 --> 00:10:33,920
 Plus I had to go pee.

136
00:10:34,719 --> 00:10:37,839
 And there was no gas stations open.

137
00:10:37,839 --> 00:10:44,240
 You could buy gas, but you could not go inside the gas station to go to the bathroom.

138
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:48,240
 And the restaurants didn't let you in unless you buy something.

139
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:51,760
 And I don't like buying something at McDonald's anyway.

140
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:54,480
 So I didn't want to do that.

141
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:57,040
 So I kept driving.

142
00:10:57,680 --> 00:11:00,640
 It was now, it was probably midnight.

143
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:02,800
 And I just kept driving.

144
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:07,360
 I knew that there would be a outhouse on the side of the road.

145
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:12,720
 There's often a place where you can pull out with your car and park for a little while.

146
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:15,440
 And there's often an outhouse.

147
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:19,600
 It's just a little toilet with a hole in the ground.

148
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:23,920
 And everybody goes to the bathroom in the outhouse.

149
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:25,680
 And so that's what I did.

150
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:28,480
 I drove probably for 20 more minutes.

151
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:31,440
 And I found one of those outhouses so that I could go pee.

152
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:36,800
 And then I decided to park my truck there and sleep for a little while.

153
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:39,440
 Because it was not safe for me to keep driving.

154
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:41,200
 Because I was so tired.

155
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,040
 And angry.

156
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:47,920
 So I slept in my truck for two or three hours.

157
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:50,240
 But I didn't really sleep.

158
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:51,599
 I was kind of cold.

159
00:11:51,599 --> 00:11:53,040
 I was uncomfortable.

160
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:58,079
 I didn't have any blankets or pillows because I wasn't planning on sleeping in my truck.

161
00:11:58,560 --> 00:12:03,599
 And so I woke up around three in the morning and I kept driving.

162
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:07,839
 The next city is called Golden.

163
00:12:07,839 --> 00:12:11,360
 And it was about three hours away from Rebelsdok.

164
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:16,960
 And there was no hotel rooms available there either.

165
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:23,920
 There was no chance of me getting a hotel room.

166
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:26,720
 Everything had been booked months ahead of time.

167
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:32,640
 And another problem I have is because I was driving a truck with a long trailer.

168
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:36,960
 So I couldn't just drive into every hotel and ask them.

169
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:39,840
 Because there was no room in the parking lots.

170
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:43,920
 So I found one hotel that had a big parking lot that I could sit in.

171
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:50,720
 And so I went to that hotel and I told the guy, I know you do not have any hotel rooms available.

172
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:56,640
 But I'm wondering if there's one place that I could sleep for like five hours.

173
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:57,120
 Please.

174
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:03,840
 I told him my whole story and I told him how desperate I was and I need to get to Calgary.

175
00:13:04,640 --> 00:13:07,760
 And I just cannot keep driving.

176
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:09,040
 I need to sleep.

177
00:13:09,040 --> 00:13:14,400
 And so he said yes, we have one where we have a person checking in at about three o'clock.

178
00:13:14,959 --> 00:13:21,520
 So that means that you need to leave at noon so that my cleaners can get in and clean the bed

179
00:13:21,520 --> 00:13:23,360
 before the next people come.

180
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,800
 And it was six in the morning.

181
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:27,839
 So I said six in the morning until noon.

182
00:13:27,839 --> 00:13:28,800
 Perfect.

183
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:29,920
 I love that.

184
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:31,120
 I'm in.

185
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:36,719
 But guess how much it cost.

186
00:13:36,719 --> 00:13:37,360
 Just guess.

187
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:38,640
 Take a wild guess.

188
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:43,600
 How much do you think this hotel room cost for six hours?

189
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:50,560
 $481.

190
00:13:53,840 --> 00:14:00,240
 And I paid it because I was so, so desperate.

191
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:06,560
 I paid $481 to sleep in a hotel room for six hours.

192
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:09,360
 Crazy.

193
00:14:09,360 --> 00:14:10,880
 Absolutely crazy.

194
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:12,240
 Have I lost my mind?

195
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:12,800
 Yes.

196
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:14,880
 I think I did lose my mind a little bit.

197
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:19,680
 But I got it back because I had a good sleep.

198
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:21,120
 I had such a good sleep.

199
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:22,320
 I had a hot shower.

200
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:27,040
 I climbed into bed and I had the best sleep for like four or five hours.

201
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:29,440
 And then I got up and kept driving.

202
00:14:30,240 --> 00:14:33,360
 I drove the last few hours to Calgary.

203
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:36,000
 And I checked into my hotel there.

204
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:42,960
 So now it was Monday afternoon, maybe like four or five o'clock in the afternoon.

205
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:46,800
 And I slept again.

206
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:49,360
 And then I got up on Tuesday.

207
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,960
 I went to the place to buy my porta-potties.

208
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:54,240
 And then I drove home.

209
00:14:54,240 --> 00:15:01,120
 I drove all the way home in one trip from Calgary back to my town.

210
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:05,760
 And it was about nine and a half hours of actual driving.

211
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:11,760
 But I stopped a lot to rest and stretch and eat some good food.

212
00:15:11,760 --> 00:15:16,960
 I don't like eating like drive through like fast food.

213
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:21,520
 So I like to stop and get something from the grocery store or get something a little bit more

214
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:26,960
 enjoyable than just fast food stuff.

215
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:30,480
 So I like to take my time when I can.

216
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:36,480
 So in total it was about a 12 or a 13 hour trip with all of my stops.

217
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:39,760
 And it's a really beautiful drive.

218
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:46,720
 I have to admit that between Calgary, Alberta and driving through the mountains in British Columbia,

219
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:49,600
 it is a beautiful landscape.

220
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:55,440
 There's amazing mountains with beautiful trees and there's waterfalls and there's rivers.

221
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:59,440
 And there's a lot of beautiful things that you can do along the way.

222
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:04,240
 But I was so annoyed that I was just driving.

223
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:09,280
 I was listening to my podcast and I just drove and I was like get me out of here.

224
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:11,040
 I hate every minute of this.

225
00:16:11,040 --> 00:16:14,960
 I just want to be home and I do not want to ever do this again.

226
00:16:15,760 --> 00:16:17,920
 But I did stop to take this picture.

227
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:21,120
 It's a pretty beautiful picture.

228
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:26,960
 It has my truck and my trailer with all of my bright green porta-potties on it.

229
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:29,760
 And it shows the mountains in the background.

230
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:36,320
 This picture was taken at Rogers Pass, which is one of the mountains on the highway

231
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:37,760
 that I was driving on.

232
00:16:37,760 --> 00:16:47,280
 And I know it's a pretty beautiful place, but I was not in a mental state to be able to enjoy it.

233
00:16:47,280 --> 00:16:48,640
 I was just so mad.

234
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:52,800
 But all in all, it worked out really well.

235
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:58,000
 We were able to get these porta-potties and give them back to all of the people

236
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,680
 that we stole porta-potties from.

237
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:04,399
 The firefighters appreciated the porta-potties that we gave them.

238
00:17:04,399 --> 00:17:10,560
 And they controlled the forest fire and nobody got hurt and nobody's properties were damaged.

239
00:17:13,119 --> 00:17:15,040
 And it all worked out.

240
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:21,200
 And I was a hero because I drove 10 hours to Caliari and 10 hours back.

241
